arwick |first=Arthur |title=The Sixties: Cultural Revolution in Britain, France, Italy, and the United States, c.1958-c.1974 |location= |publisher=Oxford University Press |year=1998 |isbn=978-0-19-210022-1 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/sixtiesculturalr00marw/page/247 247\u2013248] |url=https://archive.org/details/sixtiesculturalr00marw/page/247 }}\n* Myers, Margaret G. ''Financial History of the United States'' (1970). pp 365-510 [https://archive.org/details/financialhistory00myerrich online]\n*{{Cite book |last=O'Brien |first=Michael |title=John F. Kennedy: A Biography |year=2005 }} The most detailed scholarly biography [https://www.amazon.com/John-Kennedy-Biography-Michael-OBrien/dp/0312281293/  excerpt and text search]\n*{{Cite book |last=Olson |first=James S. |title=Historical Dictionary of the 1950s |year=2000 }} [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=11624132   online edition]\n*{{Cite book |last=Pach |first=Chester J. |lastauthoramp=yes |first2=Elmo |last2=Richardson |title=Presidency of Dwight D. Eisenhower |year=1991 }} The standard historical survey\n*{{Cite book |last=Parmet |first=Herbert S. |title=Eisenhower and the American Crusades |year=1972 }} [https://www.questia.com/PM.qst?a=o&d=14967951 online edition], scholarly biography\n*{{Cite book |last=Patterson |first=James T. |title=Grand Expectations: The United States, 1945\u20131974 |year=1988 }} Winner of the Bancroft prize in history\n*{{Cite book |last=Patterson |first=James T. |title=Restless Giant: The United States from Watergate to Bush v. Gore |year=2005 }} Survey by leading scholar\n*{{Cite book |last=Reichard |first=Gary W. |title=Politics As Usual: The Age of Truman and Eisenhower |edition=2nd |year=2004 }} 213pp; short survey\n*{{Cite book |last=Sundquist |first=James L. |title=Politics and Policy: The Eisenhower, Kennedy, and Johnson Years |year=1968 }} Excellent analysis of the major political issues of the era.\n*{{Cite book |last=Walker |first=J. Samuel |title=Prompt and Utter Des